    <centralBlocks>
      <Value><![CDATA[[
  {
    "key": "c8f99ac9-bd5d-46e5-8ba0-beff08303285",
    "name": "Why QMU?",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Why QMU?",
    "content": "<ul>\n<li>Learn real-world skills from experienced media and communications professionals and combine that with rigorous academic skills which will be of value to you throughout your career.</li>\n<li>We keep our student numbers lower than many other universities; therefor our staff can better get to know your interests, strengths and areas for development. You will find you build good collaborative relationships with students working in a range of other subjects.</li>\n<li>Build the confidence to stand on your own business feet with our Creative Entrepreneurship modules.</li>\n</ul>"
  },
  {
    "key": "c78900b5-bbc9-4256-a7f8-387cc5d1d38d",
    "name": "About the course",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "About the course",
    "content": "<p>What media and communications knowledge and skills will you need for the many roles that require them in the fast-moving world of work? You will study theories of media and communications and debate the role of media in economics, politics and society. You will look at the role of publicity, propaganda and social campaigning, and you will learn about the artistic and creative digital work that shapes the societies we live in.</p>\n<p>You will also put this theoretical understanding into action, although this is not a dedicated production course, it does have a production strand that focuses on video, audio and online content creation. You will develop your writing, management and team skills needed to produce imaginative and creative work of a high standard. During your degree you will be meeting and learning from media professionals in the fields of media and communication. In addition, you will be working with carefully selected external clients on media and communication projects.</p>\n<p>The course is designed to build your creative, critical and research skills year on year, as well as your ability to put ideas into writing and practice. Creative Entrepreneurship is a vital part of Years Three and Four. You will learn skills and approaches that will enhance your business-sense and employability. Many of our students have gone on to create their own successful companies and we have an in-house <a href=\"/services-for-business-and-industry/business-innovation-zone/\" title=\"Business Innovation Zone\">Business Innovation Zone</a> to help you get your enterprise up and running.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "f89f9116-77be-49fb-8003-d5586212be49",
    "name": "Structure",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Structure",
    "content": "<p>You can opt to study for an honours degree over four years or an ordinary degree over three years. You will complete a range of modules each year as outlined.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "ce205405-6bd1-4dcb-ac44-bbf1a80e7c7c",
    "name": "Modules",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Modules",
    "content": "<p><strong>Year One</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Media and Communications Industries</li>\n<li>Studying Media and Communications</li>\n<li>Media Analysis</li>\n<li>Digital Content Creation</li>\n<li>Media Production: Skills and Techniques</li>\n<li>Media Production: Video Project</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Year Two</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Disruption in Media and Cultural Industries</li>\n<li>Popular Media Cultures</li>\n<li>Media Client Project</li>\n<li>Media Campaigning</li>\n<li>Media Production: Digital Storytelling</li>\n<li>Media Production: Online Journalism</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Year Three</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Media, Politics &amp; Society</li>\n<li>Independent Research Project</li>\n<li>Persuasive Communication</li>\n<li>Creative Entrepreneurship: Media and Film</li>\n<li>plus two options</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Year Four</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Modernity on Screen</li>\n<li>Industry-based Learning</li>\n<li>Dissertation</li>\n<li>plus two options</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Year Three and Four options may include:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Communicating in Organisational Settings</li>\n<li>Communication, Arts and Activism</li>\n<li>Experiential Learning Placement</li>\n<li>Film Festivals</li>\n<li>Global Journalism</li>\n<li>Photography and Visual Culture</li>\n<li>Photography Practice</li>\n<li>Playwriting/Playwriting 2</li>\n<li>Political Communication</li>\n<li>Popular Music</li>\n<li>Radio and Audio Media</li>\n<li>Reputation Issues and Crisis Management</li>\n<li>Science Fiction, Fantasy and Horror</li>\n<li>Scotland on Screen</li>\n<li>Screenwriting</li>\n<li>International PR</li>\n<li>Student Initiated Module</li>\n<li>Television Drama</li>\n<li>The American West in Popular Culture</li>\n<li>The Video Essay</li>\n<li>Video Production</li>\n<li>The Only Way is Ethics</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The modules listed here are correct at time of posting (April 2021) but may differ slightly to those offered in 2022. Please check back here for any updates.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "28973da3-0a50-43ff-a9d5-3f76b5363bb1",
    "name": "Teaching, learning and assessment",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Teaching, learning and assessment",
    "content": "<p>You will learn through lectures, seminars, individual work and group work. The assessment strategy uses a range of methods to support your academic and professional development. These include: essays, reports, presentations, online discussions/postings, exams, reflective diaries, e-portfolios and content production for different media such as video, photography, website, blogs, posts and tweets.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "da1eb37a-5d6d-47da-9163-47b5e4f0b406",
    "name": "Placements",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Placements",
    "content": "<p>Work-based learning opportunities will help you build your theoretical studies into invaluable real-world skills.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "79259ff2-4a5a-4547-9d13-df33ea2c1ed6",
    "name": "Exchange opportunities",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Exchange opportunities",
    "content": "<p>In Year Three you have the opportunity (subject to availability) to study for one semester at a university overseas. For more information, see <a href=\"http://www.qmu.ac.uk/study-here/international-students/exchanges-and-study-abroad/\">Exchanges and Study Abroad</a>.</p>\n<p>On December 24th 2020, the UK Government announced that as an outcome of Brexit negotiations, the United Kingdom would not be seeking to participate in the Erasmus+ successor programme.</p>\n<p>From 2022/23 Queen Margaret University will no longer operate under the Erasmus+ scheme. Over the coming year we will be working with new and existing partners on study abroad and exchange opportunities for the 2022/23 academic year and beyond.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "9b6e3362-1c94-4d53-9fe3-0b2164deb798",
    "name": "Careers",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Careers",
    "content": "<p>This course will equip you with skills in media content creation, research, writing and communication, as well as team work and management skills. These are important for a wide range of roles such as content creation, client liaison and creative entrepreneurship. You could work in the media industries, arts management, the cultural and creative sectors or communications industries. In addition, companies in a wider range of fields are constantly looking for fresh content; they want to tell their own stories and communicate compellingly through the media with their potential customers.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "02a3f79a-31e4-48e2-8472-049dd867b187",
    "name": "Entry requirements",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Entry requirements",
    "content": "<p>Scottish Higher: Standard - BBBB, Minimum - BBCC</p>\n<p>A Level: BCC</p>\n<p>Irish Leaving Certificate: H2 H2 H3 H3</p>\n<p>International Baccalaureate: 28 points</p>\n<p>International: IELTS of 6.0 with no element lower than 5.5</p>\n<p>Required subjects: English or Media Studies preferred at Higher/A level or equivalent. English required and Maths preferred at Nat 5/GCSE.</p>\n<p>Mature/Access: Related Access course. Visit our<span> </span><a href=\"/study-here/access-to-higher-education/college-leavers-and-mature-students/\" title=\"College Leavers and Mature Students Advice\">College Leavers and Mature Students Advice page</a><span> for more information.</span> We welcome applications from mature students with other relevant qualifications and/or experience.</p>\n<p>Direct Entry:</p>\n<p><em>Year Two</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>HNC/HND in a related subject with B/CB in the graded unit</li>\n<li>Scottish Higher: BC at Advanced Higher in relevant subjects plus BB at Higher</li>\n<li>A Level: BBB in relevant subjects</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Year Three</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>HND in a related subject with CB in the graded units</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For details of related HNC and HND courses, visit our<span> </span><a href=\"/study-here/access-to-higher-education/college-leavers-and-mature-students/\" title=\"College Leavers and Mature Students Advice\">College Leavers and Mature Students Advice page</a>.</p>\n<p> </p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "f0a1ddc7-a8ec-4135-91af-8e33f2bd13b2",
    "name": "Teaching staff, class sizes and timetables",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Teaching staff, class sizes and timetables",
    "content": "<p>For more information, please see ‘<a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/363407ed108f454784361ca7c9d57713}\" title=\"How we teach and how you'll learn - Undergraduate\">How we teach and how you’ll learn’</a>.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "71017866-43db-4df9-a311-d70cef436c21",
    "name": "Awarding body",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Awarding body",
    "content": "<p>QMU. For more information, please see ‘External Review’ section on the <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/363407ed108f454784361ca7c9d57713}\" title=\"How we teach and how you'll learn - Undergraduate\" data-udi=\"umb://document/808ed3f70b49412b9304eaa6cb45dd5a\">‘How we teach and how you’ll learn</a><a href=\"/study-here/undergraduate-study/undergraduate-subject-overviews/how-we-teach-and-how-youll-learn-undergraduate/\">’</a> page.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "0367f50a-231a-45c7-9dd5-014f3c2b2aba",
    "name": "View open day course presentation",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "View open day course presentation",
    "content": "<div class=\"mceNonEditable embeditem\" data-embed-url=\"https://youtu.be/fFxZ8dSgZ7I\" data-embed-height=\"346\" data-embed-width=\"721\" data-embed-constrain=\"true\"><iframe width=\"524\" height=\"295\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/fFxZ8dSgZ7I?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"\" title=\"Media and Communications\"></iframe></div>"
  }
]]]></Value>
